{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1700160530,"nonce":"sXOQfAgVyH41qfqvs3XAU3fJsPo=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s53D5Nozk5iKpU"},"target":"84b5644489769d798a83f08bdd7c0303a39a07ebd4aff86f3eea8d07c0d26a2b","message":"toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/annotatemyids/annotatemyids/3.17.0+galaxy1\n\nWould be helpful to add an option to the bottom of the tool form to \"skip invalid IDs\".\n\nThen have the tool output a log for the IDs that were not mapped along with the primary output with mapped IDs.\n\nThis would prevent a lot of bug reports and mysterious errors. \n\n- A list could have 20 IDs -- 19 are fine, one is bad, whole process fails with a useful error message `None of the keys entered are valid keys for 'SYMBOL'. Please use the keys method to see a listing of valid arguments.`\n\n- But a list of 300 IDs -- 100 are fine, 200 are bad, whole process can fail due to exceeding memory limits at some servers (tool spins out). No message to the user, so they think it is a tool bug or server problem. Sorting valid/invalid keys would produce output for what is mappable, and some information about those that were not, with clues about the _why_.\n\nxref https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/issues/3107","files":null}]}